WEBVTT

00:00.634 --> 00:03.302
<i>Growing up, I tried to care
about father's day.</i>

00:03.304 --> 00:05.037
Happy father's day!

00:05.039 --> 00:07.339
Boy, you know
your daddy ain't here.

00:07.341 --> 00:12.111
And you better eat
every bite of that damn food!

00:12.113 --> 00:14.080
Wasting that cream of wheat.

00:14.081 --> 00:16.048
<i>But with a dad who was
a bit of a rolling stone,</i>

00:16.050 --> 00:18.117
<i>it wasn't always so easy.</i>

00:18.119 --> 00:20.152
<i>So, when I got
a family of my own,</i>

00:20.154 --> 00:23.722
<i>I made a point to be a father
my kids could celebrate.</i>

00:23.724 --> 00:27.092
<i>Unfortunately,
that didn't matter much,</i>

00:27.094 --> 00:30.062
<i>because father's day
is a damn joke.</i>

00:30.064 --> 00:33.799
<i>No love, crappy gifts,
lonely hobo breakfast.</i>

00:33.801 --> 00:36.235
<i>It pales in comparison to...</i>

00:36.237 --> 00:39.405
All: Happy mother's day! Oh!

00:39.407 --> 00:41.140
We made you a trio of omelets.

00:41.142 --> 00:42.425
Guess which one has caviar!

00:42.426 --> 00:43.709
Which one?
Hint... it's all three!

00:43.711 --> 00:45.044
[ Squeals ]

00:45.046 --> 00:46.545
Junior:
Sorry it's so small.

00:46.547 --> 00:49.481
The florist only had 60
perfect roses left. Aww.

00:49.483 --> 00:52.418
Which is why we had to call
another florist!

00:52.420 --> 00:54.620
Aw, my babies!

00:54.622 --> 00:56.088
Come get in bed!

00:56.090 --> 00:58.557
Snuggle, snuggle up with mama!

00:58.559 --> 00:59.658
Aww, get in here.

00:59.660 --> 01:01.260
Zoey: Oh, my god.

01:01.262 --> 01:02.795
Nice.
All righty.

01:02.797 --> 01:06.131
<i>But in truth, father's day
never even had a chance,</i>

01:06.133 --> 01:08.400
<i>coming just weeks after
mother's day,</i>

01:08.402 --> 01:10.202
<i>cowering in its shadow.</i>

01:10.204 --> 01:12.204
<i>Poor thing was doomed to fail.</i>

01:12.206 --> 01:14.807
<i>Basically, it's the Hanukkah
of mother's day.</i>

01:14.809 --> 01:18.777
<i>Which is why my colleagues and
I came up with a new holiday.</i>

01:18.779 --> 01:21.480
<i>Time for the world
to say hello to...</i>

01:21.482 --> 01:23.348
Rainbow: What the hell
is daddy's day?

01:27.421 --> 01:28.487
[ Sighs ]

01:33.494 --> 01:35.427
[ Air horn blows ]

01:35.429 --> 01:37.296
Hurry your asses up!

01:37.298 --> 01:39.315
All right!

01:39.316 --> 01:41.333
The daddy day rundown
is about to begin!

01:41.335 --> 01:43.168
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on!

01:43.170 --> 01:45.204
Okay, hold... hold... hold...
Hold on, sucka.

01:45.206 --> 01:46.438
That seat is reserved for Zoey.

01:46.440 --> 01:48.307
She's the oldest,

01:48.308 --> 01:50.175
and I'm gonna need her
to run point on this.

01:50.177 --> 01:51.510
You can cop
a squat on the floor.

01:51.512 --> 01:53.412
Rainbow: Dre, Dre...
He's not a dog.

01:53.414 --> 01:54.279
Sweetie, come here.
Come sit here.

01:54.281 --> 01:55.414
[ Smooches ]
Thanks, mom.

01:55.416 --> 01:56.482
All right, fine.

01:56.484 --> 01:58.100
Now, look.

01:58.101 --> 01:59.717
We're starting this new
holiday initiative at work

01:59.720 --> 02:01.386
called daddy's day.

02:01.388 --> 02:04.523
And it's everything
that father's day is not.

02:04.525 --> 02:07.359
That's why we're having it
in the fall...

02:07.361 --> 02:10.162
Far from the tyranny
of mother's day.

02:10.164 --> 02:11.296
I love mother's day.

02:11.298 --> 02:12.464
It should get a whole month.

02:12.466 --> 02:14.333
I love mom.
Love you, mom.

02:14.335 --> 02:15.901
Aww, ditto, kiddo!

02:15.903 --> 02:17.569
Who wants ice cream?!

02:17.571 --> 02:18.504
[ All cheering ]

02:18.506 --> 02:19.538
[ Air horn blows ]

02:19.540 --> 02:21.340
Oh, my goodness.

02:21.342 --> 02:22.641
Focus!

02:22.643 --> 02:25.410
I expect
professional-quality cards,

02:25.412 --> 02:28.180
each with
a heartfelt message, okay?

02:28.182 --> 02:30.582
Top-shelf gifts...
No mugs.

02:30.584 --> 02:35.854
Or ties from my closet
that I already own.

02:35.856 --> 02:37.756
All right.

02:37.758 --> 02:41.193
Now, regarding your soundtrack
of love for me.

02:41.195 --> 02:42.528
You know,
just incorporate my name

02:42.530 --> 02:43.829
into some of
the classics, like...

02:43.831 --> 02:47.733
♪ Cele-Dre good times,
come on! ♪

02:47.735 --> 02:49.401
♪ Boom, boom, boom,
let's cele-Dre ♪

02:49.403 --> 02:50.619
Rainbow: I'm sorry...
Whoo!

02:50.620 --> 02:51.836
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

02:51.839 --> 02:53.605
Huh? What?

02:53.607 --> 02:55.841
Sweetheart, did you
actually spend time at work

02:55.843 --> 02:57.643
coming up with
this ridiculous idea?

02:57.645 --> 02:58.710
Ridiculous?
Yeah.

02:58.712 --> 03:01.246
This is going to be huge!

03:01.248 --> 03:03.448
We already have
a list of potential sponsors

03:03.450 --> 03:04.683
that we're gonna pitch.

03:04.685 --> 03:07.653
Coke owns Christmas.
Hallmark owns "valentime's."

03:07.655 --> 03:09.188
Picture this...

03:09.190 --> 03:12.424
Bud light presents daddy's day!

03:12.426 --> 03:13.792
Whoo!

03:13.794 --> 03:15.694
We winning! We winning!
Dre, Dre.

03:15.696 --> 03:17.429
Hmm?

03:17.431 --> 03:20.365
There is nothing wrong
with old-school father's day.

03:20.367 --> 03:23.335
Yeah, maybe if you're
an old-school father

03:23.337 --> 03:25.204
who just came home,
downed his scotch,

03:25.206 --> 03:26.505
beat his kids,
and went to sleep.

03:26.507 --> 03:29.208
I am so tired of hearing you
whine about that.

03:29.210 --> 03:31.977
Oh, and by the way, dummy,
this is the dumbest idea

03:31.979 --> 03:33.612
of all the dumb ideas
you ever had.

03:33.614 --> 03:35.380
See?

03:35.382 --> 03:37.916
This sweet kiss of sunshine
is the dude

03:37.918 --> 03:40.552
that father's day was built for.

03:40.554 --> 03:41.987
Me, I'm different.

03:41.989 --> 03:43.789
I take my kids
to soccer practice.

03:43.791 --> 03:45.824
I help my children
with they homework.

03:45.826 --> 03:48.360
I wore a bjorn, damn it!

03:48.362 --> 03:49.928
Is that
that little half-bra

03:49.930 --> 03:51.663
with the baby
hanging out the front?

03:51.665 --> 03:53.732
You know, you really ought to
stop mentioning that, son.

03:53.734 --> 03:57.636
Ooh, a family meeting.
I'll be in my room.

03:57.638 --> 03:58.604
Come on, resheida.

03:58.605 --> 03:59.571
Hey, hey, hey,
hold... hold... hold...

03:59.573 --> 04:01.340
Where are you going?

04:01.342 --> 04:04.977
To my room. I... I just said that.
Perfect example.

04:04.979 --> 04:07.613
Had you spoken to
an old-school father that way,

04:07.615 --> 04:09.881
he would have knocked
all your teeth out.

04:09.883 --> 04:11.817
Wisdom teeth included.
See?

04:11.819 --> 04:13.652
You know what?
I'm gonna call myself an uber,

04:13.654 --> 04:15.320
'cause it looks like
you about to get a whoopin'.

04:15.322 --> 04:16.655
Okay, look.
I'll make it quick, all right?

04:16.657 --> 04:18.023
There's a new holiday...
Daddy's day...

04:18.025 --> 04:19.691
Sweeping the nation,

04:19.693 --> 04:22.494
spearheaded by your main man,
driggity.

04:22.496 --> 04:24.730
Okay, you girls should go. Yeah.

04:24.732 --> 04:25.864
All right, you have till Sunday!

04:25.866 --> 04:27.566
No.
[ Air horn blows ]

04:27.568 --> 04:28.834
[ All shouting ]
Come on!

04:28.836 --> 04:29.901
Dismissed!

04:34.441 --> 04:37.009
Hey, thanks for sticking up
for me earlier, mom.

04:37.011 --> 04:40.012
You know, letting me sit on
the couch like a human and all.

04:40.014 --> 04:41.847
Aww, yeah,
your dad is hard on you.

04:41.849 --> 04:43.982
He is, right?!
Yeah.

04:43.984 --> 04:46.485
Me and my blog aren't
the only ones who see it.

04:46.487 --> 04:48.387
Mnh-mnh.

04:48.389 --> 04:49.554
Look, take the night off.

04:49.556 --> 04:51.056
Kick your feet up.

04:51.058 --> 04:52.457
I got the laundry.

04:52.459 --> 04:54.559
Really?

04:54.561 --> 04:56.728
You're just buttering me up
'cause you want, like,

04:56.730 --> 04:57.996
a new wizard hat or something.

04:57.998 --> 04:59.564
No, I'm just giving back

04:59.566 --> 05:01.433
to someone who gives me
endless love.

05:01.435 --> 05:03.769
Shut it!

05:03.771 --> 05:08.473
Aw, my sweet baby boy.

05:08.475 --> 05:09.508
[ Laughs ]

05:09.510 --> 05:10.742
[ Laughs ]

05:10.744 --> 05:13.011
You got a good kid there.
I know.

05:13.013 --> 05:15.580
I mean, he's like...
He's like a peach.

05:15.582 --> 05:16.815
Look at him.

05:16.817 --> 05:18.550
It just shows he loves you.
Yeah.

05:18.552 --> 05:21.653
No matter how disappointing
you are as a mother.

05:29.797 --> 05:31.496
Recycle that.

05:32.499 --> 05:34.499
Aw, man.

05:34.501 --> 05:36.835
This makes me want to be
a daddy so baddy. Ugh.

05:36.837 --> 05:38.570
Hey, is it true
that babies have to love you,

05:38.572 --> 05:39.905
no matter what?

05:39.907 --> 05:42.474
Depends... can you fill
your breasts with milk?

05:42.476 --> 05:44.009
Bruh, just carry a pocket
full of sugar with you.

05:44.011 --> 05:46.511
That's why babies call me
the snowman.

05:46.513 --> 05:47.979
Stevens: Guys,
this is a great idea,

05:47.981 --> 05:50.716
but where is
the global reach, huh?

05:50.718 --> 05:53.885
We have got to cram this idea
down the world's throat.

05:53.887 --> 05:56.088
Dre: What if
we custom-branded the day

05:56.090 --> 05:57.489
for each international market?

05:57.491 --> 06:00.125
Like, St. dad-Rick's day
in Ireland.

06:00.127 --> 06:01.827
Outstanding.

06:01.829 --> 06:05.030
[ German accent ] Get ready
for pop-toberfest, Germany!

06:05.032 --> 06:07.833
[ Laughter ]

06:07.835 --> 06:10.902
What about our low-riding
hombres south of the border?

06:10.904 --> 06:12.604
Cinco de daddio.

06:12.606 --> 06:14.039
Olé!

06:14.041 --> 06:16.375
Bonjour,
dads-tille day!

06:16.377 --> 06:17.377
[ Chuckles ]

06:20.381 --> 06:21.880
What? I'm sorry.

06:21.882 --> 06:23.782
I thought we were just
vomiting out bad ideas.

06:23.784 --> 06:25.717
Is that not... Well, of course
you don't understand, Lucy,

06:25.719 --> 06:27.486
because you're not a father.

06:27.488 --> 06:30.422
So until you have sired
two beautiful baby boys,

06:30.424 --> 06:33.425
shipped them away at the age
of 3 to a Swiss boarding school,

06:33.427 --> 06:35.827
and then bribed
a U.S. senator to get them off

06:35.829 --> 06:39.064
separate but equally gruesome
murder charges,

06:39.066 --> 06:41.533
you stand down there, sweet pea.

06:41.535 --> 06:44.903
Dre, how's the casting going
for the daddy's day commercial?

06:44.905 --> 06:46.438
I haven't found
the perfect kid yet.

06:46.440 --> 06:48.740
Dre, we have got to
get this right.

06:48.742 --> 06:51.076
Now, if we cannot sell
this idea stateside,

06:51.078 --> 06:53.412
how on earth
are we gonna sell rama-dad?

06:53.414 --> 06:55.147
Charlie: Yeah, Dre,
this is important.

06:55.149 --> 06:57.983
Me helping craft out
a strong view on fatherhood

06:57.985 --> 06:59.484
would look really good
in front of a judge

06:59.486 --> 07:00.752
at my son's custody hearing.

07:00.754 --> 07:01.887
[ Chuckles ]

07:01.889 --> 07:04.423
Oh, crap.
It was yesterday.

07:04.425 --> 07:06.591
Well, let me go call eustace
and tell him goodbye.

07:09.530 --> 07:13.031
Look, what we need is a real kid
with real energy, right?

07:13.033 --> 07:14.599
But not fat. People hate fat.
Ugh.

07:14.601 --> 07:16.284
Dre.
Hmm?

07:16.285 --> 07:17.968
What about casting
your daughter, Scott?

07:19.072 --> 07:21.106
Zoey? Whatever. Would she do it?

07:21.108 --> 07:24.676
I mean, she is beautiful
and racially ambiguous.

07:24.678 --> 07:27.579
No one can be mad.

07:27.581 --> 07:29.565
Great idea.

07:29.566 --> 07:31.550
Offensively put, but I think
I can make that happen.

07:31.552 --> 07:32.884
Boom.

07:32.886 --> 07:35.654
Shackalacka.

07:35.656 --> 07:38.757
<i>Zoey's face was right,
but her attitude was wrong.</i>

07:38.759 --> 07:41.460
<i>If I was going to get her
psyched about daddy's day,</i>

07:41.462 --> 07:43.895
<i>I need to get her psyched
about daddy.</i>

07:43.897 --> 07:46.064
[ Knock on door ]
Knock, knock!

07:46.066 --> 07:51.203
Who wants a driving lesson
in daddy's Benz?

07:51.205 --> 07:54.840
Hey, Zoey, will you stop texting
and answer me?

07:54.842 --> 07:56.641
Oh, I just texted you no.

07:56.643 --> 07:58.510
What are you talking about?

07:58.512 --> 08:01.246
You've been begging
for more lessons for months.

08:01.248 --> 08:03.181
Yeah, but you're not exactly
the best teacher.

08:03.183 --> 08:04.616
You get a little yelly.

08:04.618 --> 08:06.651
Yelling is caring.

08:06.653 --> 08:08.220
Resheida:
Oh, yo, Mr. j.,

08:08.222 --> 08:09.505
did Zoey tell you

08:09.506 --> 08:10.789
I've been thinking about
that daddy's day thing?

08:10.791 --> 08:13.492
No, I did not.

08:13.494 --> 08:15.560
Real talk, you need to change it
from Sunday to Monday.

08:15.562 --> 08:17.996
But that's Columbus day.
Pfft, and?

08:17.998 --> 08:20.198
Everybody knows Columbus day
is, like, crazy racist.

08:20.200 --> 08:22.734
So, you just put daddy's day
in there

08:22.736 --> 08:23.702
and make it
a three-day weekend.

08:23.704 --> 08:26.938
Okay.
I'm intrigued.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.540
You've got your barbecue
on Saturday,

08:28.542 --> 08:31.142
white linen party on Sunday,
and then Monday,

08:31.144 --> 08:33.645
you get to kick back
and get your daddy on.

08:33.647 --> 08:35.914
Wow.
I'm not gonna lie, Resheida.

08:35.916 --> 08:38.016
You've cracked this wide open.

08:38.018 --> 08:39.651
Well, I don't really
get to see my dad,

08:39.653 --> 08:42.654
so I think the ones that stick
around should be celebrated.

08:44.191 --> 08:45.557
See that, Zoey?

08:45.559 --> 08:47.158
Your sad friend gets it.

08:47.160 --> 08:49.160
Before I got my scholarship
to valley prep,

08:49.162 --> 08:51.062
seeing a daddy
was like seeing a unicorn.

08:51.064 --> 08:52.297
You know, in my neighborhood,

08:52.299 --> 08:54.232
when there's a man
in someone's house,

08:54.234 --> 08:56.034
we usually just call the cops.

08:56.036 --> 08:58.036
Oh, my god.
They still do that?

08:58.038 --> 09:01.606
Zoey: Dad.
Can you please go?

09:01.608 --> 09:03.074
And next time you have
what looks to be a Kale salad,

09:03.076 --> 09:05.196
you may want to floss
before you start a conversation.

09:08.982 --> 09:10.949
Resheida,
how would you like to be

09:10.951 --> 09:13.718
the official face
of daddy's day?

09:13.720 --> 09:14.286
Really?
Really?

09:14.288 --> 09:15.754
Yes.

09:15.756 --> 09:17.822
I can't think
of anyone more deserving.

09:17.824 --> 09:19.558
Now, let me go get some floss.

09:19.560 --> 09:20.959
Then we can go over
the storyboards

09:20.961 --> 09:21.793
about the commercial.

09:21.795 --> 09:23.261
Okay.

09:23.263 --> 09:25.697
<i>Harsh lesson for Zoey to learn,</i>

09:25.699 --> 09:27.165
<i>but maybe this would teach her</i>

09:27.167 --> 09:30.001
<i>to respect her cool,
involved dad.</i>

09:30.003 --> 09:31.303
Damn.
Did I swallow anything?

09:35.242 --> 09:37.709
A little help, please!
Bags ripping!

09:37.711 --> 09:39.811
All eggs and bottles!

09:39.813 --> 09:41.746
What are you doing, mom?

09:41.748 --> 09:43.615
You don't need to be
coming home from work

09:43.617 --> 09:45.116
and starting a whole other job.

09:45.118 --> 09:47.052
Here.

09:47.054 --> 09:48.219
I made you chamomile.
What?

09:48.221 --> 09:50.221
Aww.

09:50.223 --> 09:53.058
My sweet, little, thoughtful
love bug.

09:53.894 --> 09:55.860
Diane: Mom!
Starving!

09:55.862 --> 09:56.828
[ Groans ]

09:56.830 --> 09:57.862
I can't even deal.

09:57.864 --> 09:59.197
Understood.

09:59.199 --> 10:01.166
Hey, guys,
your mom's had a long day.

10:01.168 --> 10:03.001
But...
And no backtalk!

10:03.003 --> 10:05.370
If you only knew
how much she does for you!

10:05.372 --> 10:06.338
Now go clean your room!

10:06.340 --> 10:08.039
But we...
Quietly.

10:14.781 --> 10:17.649
Nicely done.
I learned from the best.

10:17.651 --> 10:18.917
Aw, sheesh.

10:18.919 --> 10:20.619
[ Laughs ]

10:20.621 --> 10:22.654
Oh, I had a day from hell.

10:22.656 --> 10:24.623
Well, you're standing
in a field of corn,

10:24.625 --> 10:26.625
'cause I'm all ears.

10:26.627 --> 10:28.126
Oh, shush.

10:28.128 --> 10:31.696
That is how the world
will meet daddy's day.

10:31.698 --> 10:33.798
This is...
This is dope, Mr. j.

10:33.800 --> 10:36.134
I mean, like,
you're a genius or something.

10:36.136 --> 10:37.669
Oh, please.
I don't need to hear that crap.

10:37.671 --> 10:39.170
But, you know,

10:39.172 --> 10:40.805
you can go ahead
and tell other people.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.707
All right.
All right.

10:42.709 --> 10:45.043
Dre, I got to say,

10:45.045 --> 10:47.712
it's kind of screwed up
that you cast Zoey's friend

10:47.714 --> 10:50.048
as the face of daddy's day
instead of your own daughter.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.916
No, you know what's screwed up?
Hmm?

10:51.918 --> 10:53.218
The fact
that Zoey doesn't appreciate

10:53.220 --> 10:55.086
that she<i> has</i> a father.

10:55.088 --> 10:56.921
All right,
when I was growing up, hell,

10:56.923 --> 10:58.223
hardly anybody had a daddy.

10:58.225 --> 10:59.858
What are you talking about?
Your dad was around.

10:59.860 --> 11:01.793
Ehh...

11:01.795 --> 11:03.194
But that's what a dad did.

11:03.196 --> 11:04.629
I mean, I claimed you,

11:04.630 --> 11:06.063
provided you with food,
shelter, clothing,

11:06.066 --> 11:07.032
whooped your ass,
and went to the track.

11:07.034 --> 11:08.400
Of course.

11:08.401 --> 11:09.767
I did a year's worth
of parenting

11:09.770 --> 11:10.902
in a fraction of the time.

11:10.904 --> 11:12.337
It was surgical daddy.

11:13.240 --> 11:14.939
It was deadbeat daddy.

11:14.941 --> 11:15.974
Mm-hmm.

11:15.976 --> 11:16.908
Call it what you want.

11:16.910 --> 11:18.309
I got in and I got out

11:18.311 --> 11:20.311
and saved the mess
that you made.

11:20.313 --> 11:22.681
I was the Mariano Rivera
of fatherhood...

11:22.683 --> 11:24.049
Hall of fame bound.

11:24.051 --> 11:25.784
Ruby:
Oh, you were the worst.

11:25.786 --> 11:27.786
But Dre's one hell of a father.

11:27.788 --> 11:29.421
He even wore that bra thing.

11:29.423 --> 11:30.822
Sure did.

11:30.824 --> 11:32.290
Wore it once.
Used it wrong.

11:32.292 --> 11:33.958
May have cut off Jack's oxygen.

11:33.960 --> 11:35.293
We don't know.
We know.

11:35.295 --> 11:37.228
Yeah. We know. Well, we know.

11:37.230 --> 11:38.797
Look, look, look, look...
The point is,

11:38.799 --> 11:42.267
you want your kids
to acknowledge all you do.

11:42.269 --> 11:44.369
Especially
your firstborn baby girl.

11:44.371 --> 11:47.038
Hell, all a dad ever wants
is the love of his daughter.

11:47.040 --> 11:50.625
Frankly speaking,

11:50.626 --> 11:54.211
a son is just a disappointing
photocopy of yourself.

11:54.214 --> 11:58.183
He wrote that
in my 10th birthday card.

11:58.185 --> 12:02.153
[ Piano music plays ]

12:10.097 --> 12:12.063
Announcer:
There are many ways to say it,

12:12.065 --> 12:14.499
but only one man
who deserves to hear it.

12:14.501 --> 12:16.334
Who's your daddy?

12:16.336 --> 12:17.802
Daddy's day.

12:19.773 --> 12:21.840
Ooh, black man.

12:21.842 --> 12:22.974
All right?

12:22.976 --> 12:24.209
[ Applause ]

12:24.211 --> 12:27.912
God is on his side.
Outstanding, Dre.

12:27.914 --> 12:30.148
We are gonna make a fortune.

12:30.150 --> 12:33.251
This must be how Jesus felt
when he invented Christmas.

12:33.253 --> 12:35.954
Dre: Okay, hey, guys, so,
without further ado,

12:35.956 --> 12:38.990
I'd like to introduce you...

12:38.992 --> 12:42.127
To the face of daddy's day.

12:42.129 --> 12:44.929
[ Gasps ] She exists.
I thought she was C.G.!

12:44.931 --> 12:46.331
And to think,

12:46.333 --> 12:48.433
this lovely little angel
doesn't even have a daddy

12:48.435 --> 12:49.868
to soak in all that love.

12:49.870 --> 12:52.237
She's a bastard.

12:52.239 --> 12:54.906
She seems so normal and clean,

12:54.908 --> 12:57.242
like a loved girl
who will turn out okay,

12:57.244 --> 12:59.410
instead of what's really
gonna happen to her.

12:59.412 --> 13:01.846
Okay, now I'm getting sad.

13:03.250 --> 13:05.033
[ Cellphone chimes ]

13:05.034 --> 13:06.817
Zoey: Mom,
Resheida just texted me

13:06.820 --> 13:08.853
and said dad's giving her
a driving lesson.

13:08.855 --> 13:10.388
Yeah, I know.

13:10.390 --> 13:12.290
But don't let it bother you,
sweetie.

13:12.292 --> 13:14.259
I mean, she doesn't have anyone
to teach her how to drive,

13:14.261 --> 13:16.261
and you guys both
have that test.

13:16.263 --> 13:17.713
Okay.

13:17.714 --> 13:19.164
If that's how
you want to play it,

13:19.166 --> 13:23.301
game on, square man.

13:23.303 --> 13:24.869
How's the pressure?

13:24.871 --> 13:27.438
Don't hold back, sweetie.
Mama's not made of glass.

13:27.440 --> 13:29.240
All right.

13:29.242 --> 13:31.976
Parallel parking...
It's the hardest part.

13:31.978 --> 13:33.444
It's so hard,
they didn't even try it

13:33.446 --> 13:36.314
in any of
the "fast and furiouseseses."

13:36.316 --> 13:38.550
Cool. Okay, I'm just gonna
need you to relax, okay?

13:38.552 --> 13:40.185
Okay. All right.
All right, go.

13:40.187 --> 13:42.020
All right. Back it up. Cut
the wheel to the right.

13:42.022 --> 13:43.939
Cut the wheel down hard!

13:43.940 --> 13:45.857
Stop, stop!
It's a high curb, low door.

13:45.859 --> 13:48.126
Oh, lord.
Okay.

13:48.128 --> 13:49.194
Back it up?
Back it on up.

13:49.196 --> 13:50.128
Too fast!

13:50.130 --> 13:51.196
Cut it!

13:51.198 --> 13:52.564
Cut it!

13:52.565 --> 13:53.931
Ain't nothing parallel
about this.

13:53.934 --> 13:55.433
Ain't nothing parallel!

13:55.435 --> 13:56.501
Did you just get up on the curb?

13:56.503 --> 13:58.236
Aw, baby, that's my rim!

13:58.238 --> 14:00.038
That's my rim!

14:00.040 --> 14:01.606
Not bad.

14:01.608 --> 14:03.408
Hey, I'm sorry I was
a little tough on you.

14:03.410 --> 14:06.511
I've been told that,
you know, I'm a yeller.

14:06.513 --> 14:09.013
[ Laughs ]
Well, yelling is caring.

14:11.952 --> 14:15.286
[ Gasps ]
Uh, Mr. j., you good?

14:15.288 --> 14:16.888
I'm good.
It's... it's...

14:16.890 --> 14:19.924
It's just
that someone finally gets me.

14:19.926 --> 14:21.860
Charlie: Watch out.
Baby driver coming through.

14:24.464 --> 14:26.931
What up, big d.?

14:29.603 --> 14:31.336
♪ Drive slow, homie ♪

14:31.338 --> 14:33.371
Now, when you see the police,
keep going, all right?

14:33.373 --> 14:34.939
Onward to the liquor store!

14:34.941 --> 14:36.608
♪ Drive slow, homie ♪

14:36.610 --> 14:40.345
<i>Zoey had fired her first shot,
and it was a good one.</i>

14:40.347 --> 14:42.914
♪ You never know, homie ♪
rainbow: Oh, shoot.

14:42.916 --> 14:45.450
I left all the hamburger
in the car?

14:45.452 --> 14:47.518
[ Groans ]

14:47.520 --> 14:50.021
That meat
has just been festering

14:50.023 --> 14:52.123
in that hot trunk
for, like, two days.

14:52.125 --> 14:54.959
Don't worry, mom.
Juju's got this.

14:54.961 --> 14:57.295
I'm s... I'm sorry,
who's... who's... who's juju?

14:57.297 --> 14:59.397
See?

14:59.399 --> 15:02.533
Throw him a little love,
he'll do anything for you.

15:02.535 --> 15:04.569
I know.
It's like he'd die for me.

15:04.571 --> 15:06.337
Yeah.
[ Laughs ]

15:06.339 --> 15:11.676
But the real question is...
Is will he kill for you?

15:11.678 --> 15:14.946
Why would that be the question?

15:14.948 --> 15:16.514
There will be a day.

15:16.516 --> 15:18.483
There always is.

15:18.485 --> 15:19.918
A day...

15:19.920 --> 15:21.352
What?

15:21.354 --> 15:24.022
I don't...
Um, okay.

15:24.024 --> 15:28.393
<i>So Zoey and I were locked in a
major daddy-daughter standoff.</i>

15:28.395 --> 15:29.360
Hello, Zoey.

15:29.362 --> 15:30.695
Hello, "daddy."

15:30.697 --> 15:32.096
Hope you're happy.

15:32.098 --> 15:34.933
I failed
my driver's ed test so bad

15:34.935 --> 15:37.235
I'm not allowed to take
the real one for three months.

15:37.237 --> 15:39.704
And this is on me how?

15:39.706 --> 15:42.407
Your boy Charlie
is a horrible teacher.

15:42.409 --> 15:45.410
The instructor said
I drove like a drunk person.

15:45.412 --> 15:48.046
She actually
gave me a breathalyzer.

15:48.048 --> 15:49.714
Again, I don't see
how this is my fault.

15:49.716 --> 15:52.150
You turned down my lessons.

15:52.152 --> 15:54.686
I'm a teenager.
That's my job.

15:54.688 --> 15:56.521
You're supposed to rise above it

15:56.523 --> 15:59.357
and force me to take
your lessons like a good dad.

15:59.359 --> 16:03.094
But, no, instead,
you taught Resheida how to drive

16:03.096 --> 16:06.698
and put her
in your stupid commercial.

16:06.700 --> 16:08.032
Zoey...

16:10.270 --> 16:13.638
♪ Cele-Dre good times,
come on! ♪

16:13.640 --> 16:16.708
♪ It's a cele-dretion ♪

16:20.347 --> 16:21.646
So I was not really feeling like
the number-one dad in the world,

16:21.648 --> 16:23.614
which is not what you want

16:23.616 --> 16:25.483
when you're about to pitch
a bunch of sponsors

16:25.485 --> 16:27.452
on the concept of daddy's day.

16:27.454 --> 16:29.721
Stevens:
Take it away, Dre.

16:29.723 --> 16:31.456
Dre.
Hmm?

16:31.458 --> 16:32.223
Here we go.

16:32.225 --> 16:33.558
Oh. Oh, my bad.

16:33.560 --> 16:36.361
Uh, sorry. Okay.
All right.

16:36.363 --> 16:37.428
Uh, so, uh...

16:37.430 --> 16:39.030
Here we go.

16:39.032 --> 16:42.767
Uh, we've prepared a pitch...

16:42.769 --> 16:45.303
Uh, very big.

16:45.305 --> 16:46.304
Very big.

16:46.306 --> 16:48.306
It appeals to people...

16:48.308 --> 16:49.640
Um...

16:49.642 --> 16:53.411
Mostly men.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.146
Yeah, just...

16:55.148 --> 16:57.615
And the people that they make.

16:57.617 --> 16:59.650
So I guess
we can call them kids.

16:59.652 --> 17:02.020
All right?

17:02.022 --> 17:03.021
All right, let's just...
Yeah.

17:03.023 --> 17:04.589
Uh...

17:06.760 --> 17:08.226
[ Clears throat ]

17:08.228 --> 17:12.597
I got some, um... Focus powder
in my office.

17:12.599 --> 17:14.665
Just say the word.

17:14.667 --> 17:17.201
Uh, look...
Guys, I'm sorry.

17:17.203 --> 17:20.104
Uh, I'm... I'm just
a little distracted.

17:20.106 --> 17:20.705
Uh, you see...

17:20.707 --> 17:23.307
[ Sighs ]

17:23.309 --> 17:24.742
I've been using
my daughter's friend.

17:24.744 --> 17:26.210
[ Groaning ]

17:26.212 --> 17:27.445
No, no, no, no...
Not that way.

17:27.447 --> 17:28.546
Not that way.

17:28.548 --> 17:30.248
She's very young.

17:30.250 --> 17:31.582
No. Dre. No.
Very young.

17:31.584 --> 17:35.286
But she reminds me
of my daughter, okay?

17:35.288 --> 17:37.522
And...

17:37.524 --> 17:40.458
She gives me things
that my daughter won't.

17:40.460 --> 17:42.727
Sponsor executive: Okay.
I think we've heard enough.

17:42.729 --> 17:44.209
We'd rather not be implicated
in this.

17:46.232 --> 17:47.532
I just...

17:48.435 --> 17:49.734
Daddy's day.

17:49.736 --> 17:52.070
Well, I'm-a go get focused.

17:54.741 --> 17:57.075
Zoey: I can't believe
you passed.

17:57.077 --> 17:59.544
You're gonna have
a driver's license and no dad...

17:59.546 --> 18:01.746
Living the dream.

18:01.748 --> 18:03.414
Look, anybody is better
than my dad.

18:03.416 --> 18:05.316
Okay, I think
he follows me on instagram,

18:05.318 --> 18:07.552
but he hasn't liked
any of my pics yet.

18:07.554 --> 18:08.686
Worthless punk.

18:08.688 --> 18:10.188
Pop:
Listen, Zo-Zo...

18:10.190 --> 18:12.490
Uh, as a son,
he's a complete disappointment,

18:12.492 --> 18:14.459
but as a father, you have
nothing to complain about.

18:14.461 --> 18:17.295
I mean, if he did the things
that he does for you

18:17.297 --> 18:19.697
back in<i> my</i> day,
he'd be considered a woman,

18:19.699 --> 18:21.866
so, you know, give him a break.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.471
You fed my babies car meat?!

18:26.473 --> 18:28.639
[ Retching ] Well, you
were so mad at yourself

18:28.641 --> 18:30.007
for leaving it out there,

18:30.008 --> 18:31.374
I tried to save it
so you wouldn't feel bad.

18:31.377 --> 18:32.743
[ Retching ]

18:32.745 --> 18:34.679
Junior...
I'm sorry.

18:34.681 --> 18:36.814
I was just trying to help.
Why?!

18:36.816 --> 18:43.421
You always look so,
so, so, so very tired.

18:43.423 --> 18:46.591
Oh, well...
Th-that's very sweet.

18:46.593 --> 18:48.860
Look, junior,
why don't you go upstairs?

18:48.862 --> 18:51.362
Maybe later we can watch
a movie together.

18:51.364 --> 18:53.197
Sweet.
I love you.

18:53.199 --> 18:55.233
Oh, I love you, too, sweetheart.

18:55.235 --> 18:56.901
Now,<i> that's</i> how you raise a man.

18:56.903 --> 18:58.620
[ Chuckles ]

18:58.621 --> 19:00.338
Trust me,
it's the best relationship

19:00.340 --> 19:01.706
either of you will ever have.

19:01.708 --> 19:05.276
Like me and my Dre.

19:05.278 --> 19:07.578
I remember the first time
Dre cooked car meat.

19:07.580 --> 19:09.580
He got so upset,

19:09.582 --> 19:12.283
I let him stay in the bath
with me an extra two hours.

19:12.285 --> 19:14.218
No.

19:14.220 --> 19:15.286
No. Okay, no.

19:15.288 --> 19:16.838
No.

19:16.839 --> 19:18.389
The whole Dre-and-Ruby
freak show

19:18.391 --> 19:21.359
is not what's happening
between me and my boy, okay?

19:21.361 --> 19:22.693
Okay.

19:22.695 --> 19:25.429
Junior: Mom?
I cued up "before sunrise."

19:25.431 --> 19:28.332
We're snuggling
in<i> your</i> bed, right?

19:28.334 --> 19:29.567
[ Cackles ]

19:29.569 --> 19:31.702
Oh, god.

19:31.704 --> 19:33.571
Oh, god, I've shown
that boy too much love.

19:33.573 --> 19:35.573
Mm-hmm.
Ugh.

19:35.575 --> 19:37.575
<i>I had dropped the ball at work,</i>

19:37.577 --> 19:40.478
<i>but I wasn't going to
keep dropping it at home.</i>

19:40.480 --> 19:43.548
<i>I needed to talk to Zoey,
but before I could,</i>

19:43.550 --> 19:44.448
<i>she made her move.</i>

19:44.450 --> 19:46.584
All: Happy daddy's day!

19:46.586 --> 19:50.354
Zoey: Release
daddy's pearls of wisdom.

19:50.356 --> 19:52.890
Oh!

19:52.892 --> 19:55.393
Present
daddy's feast of strength.

19:55.395 --> 19:56.661
Wow.

19:56.663 --> 19:58.229
The first two stations
of the daddy.

19:58.231 --> 20:00.865
Zo-Zo, you pulled all this
together for me?

20:00.867 --> 20:03.668
Well, I mean,
you're still really embarrassing

20:03.670 --> 20:06.437
and annoying, but...

20:06.439 --> 20:08.239
At least you're here.

20:08.241 --> 20:10.641
Our dad.

20:10.643 --> 20:12.543
Daddy.
Nope, not happening.

20:12.545 --> 20:14.378
Fair enough.

20:14.380 --> 20:18.216
So, did you find a sponsor
for your brilliant little idea?

20:18.218 --> 20:21.485
Long story,
but maybe Megan's law.

20:21.487 --> 20:22.887
[ Clattering ]

20:22.889 --> 20:25.389
Damn it, boy!
You dropped the ribs?!

20:25.391 --> 20:27.858
Go outside and think about
what you just did.

20:27.860 --> 20:31.295
Mom, I...
Listen to your father.

20:31.297 --> 20:33.431
And, uh, listen here.

20:33.433 --> 20:36.367
Nothing personal,
but from now on,

20:36.369 --> 20:39.837
we're gonna be
just a normal mother and son.

20:39.839 --> 20:41.906
Okay?

20:43.243 --> 20:46.744
Now he'll never kill anyone
for you.

20:46.746 --> 20:48.446
That's why I didn't...

20:51.784 --> 20:54.385
♪♪

20:58.958 --> 21:01.325
[ Sighs ]

21:01.327 --> 21:02.660
[ Knock on door ]

21:03.696 --> 21:05.663
Left alone all day,
11:59,

21:05.665 --> 21:07.932
here you come
with a bottle of scotch.

21:09.569 --> 21:11.936
Damn, I love daddy's day.
[ Chuckles ]

21:11.938 --> 21:13.871
Do you want to have a drink?
Oh, yes, sir.

21:18.011 --> 21:19.011
Ahh.
